  "text": "In the beginning, research on technology acceptance concentrated on new occupational software in organizations and institutions [CITATION_1] . Research presented in this paper focuses on web-enabled software in private use, with private data being processed and stored. In our paper, we focus on the influence of personality traits on technology acceptance. Many new products are not only unfamiliar or evoke resistance just because things are different than before. Furthermore, there is an increasing risk to lose privacy or money. That is why we pick up approaches that integrate trust in models for technology acceptance [CITATION_2] .",
